Section 2: Dockerfile Basics
Dockerfile:
FROM node:18
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN npm install
CMD ["node", "app.js"]
Questions
What happens at each step?
What is cached?
What happens if only app.js changes?
Why CMD instead of RUN?
Solutions:- 

1. Step-by-step
Instruction	       What it does
FROM	             Base image
WORKDIR	           Sets working dir
COPY	             Copies files
RUN                Installs dependencies
CMD	               Default runtime command

Each creates a layer

2. What is cached?
Docker caches layers
If no change → layer reused
If change → rebuild from that step
3. Change only app.js
COPY . . changes → cache breaks
RUN npm install runs again ❌

This is inefficient (we fix later)

4. CMD vs RUN
RUN	                  CMD
Build time	          Runtime
Executes immediately	Executes on container start
